When I speake of ecclesiastieal writers, I meane of such, as were before the wicked vsurpation of the Sea of Rome was growne so vnmeasurablie greate, that not onely with tyrannicall power, but also with corrupt doctrine, yt be- ganne to subuerte Christes gospell, and to turne the state that Christ and his Apostles sett in the church vpside downe.
